HEADWORD: Sycones
<hw>Sy*co"nes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a fig.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of calcareous
sponges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They usually resemble a fig, being vase-shaped with a
fringed opening at the summit. The feeding cells are in ampullae
connected with radial tubes in the thickened walls of the
body.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

